# ACC v2 — Cursor Rules
# Cursor is the code implementation agent. Claude (via ACC Task Bus) is the architect.
# Read tasks/current-task.md before starting any implementation.

## Project Structure
- Backend: cloud/ (Node.js CommonJS, Express)
- Frontend: ui/ (React + Vite + Tailwind)
- Desktop: desktop/ (Electron)
- Task Bus: cloud/taskbus/ (store, router, providerFallback)
- Bot: cloud/telegram/bot.js
- Config: pm2.config.js, railway.json, Dockerfile

## Primary AI Provider
- DeepSeek is primary (DEEPSEEK_API_KEY in .env)
- Claude is fallback only (balance depleted)
- All AI calls go through cloud/taskbus/providerFallback.js

## SAFETY RULES — NEVER VIOLATE
- NEVER use REDACTED Railway API tokens for destructive operations
- NEVER delete files without explicit confirmation from Shayan
- NEVER modify .env directly — only read it
- NEVER run database migrations without Shayan approval
- NEVER push directly to main/master on Railway-connected repos
- NEVER expose secrets in code, logs, or commits
- ALWAYS use sandbox mode for marketplace/external actions

## Workflow
1. Read tasks/current-task.md for the current task spec
2. Implement ONLY what the spec says — no scope creep
3. Run: node _servertest.js to verify server loads
4. Commit with clear message matching task title
5. Push to GitHub — Railway auto-deploys staging

## Code Style
- CommonJS (require/module.exports) for cloud/
- ES modules (import/export) for ui/
- No TypeScript in cloud/ — plain JavaScript only
- Always add error handling — never let errors swallow silently
- Log format: [module] message (e.g. [airtable] Connected)

## Adding a new connector
1. File: cloud/connectors/<name>.js
2. Export: { checkHealth, enabled }
3. Add warning if API key missing
4. Register in cloud/connectors/registry.js
5. Add key to .env.example

## Adding a Telegram command
1. Edit cloud/taskbus/telegramCommands.js
2. Add exact match in handleTaskBusCommand()
3. Always wrap in try/catch run() wrapper
4. Use safeSend() not sendFn() directly — strips Markdown that breaks Telegram

## Testing
- Syntax: node --check <file>
- Server load: node _servertest.js (create if needed)
- Task Bus: POST http://localhost:4000/api/taskbus/task
- Health: GET http://localhost:4000/api/health

## Git
- Branch: master
- Remote: https://github.com/Thatisshayan/ACC.git
- PM2 manages local processes — never kill node.exe manually
- After push: Railway auto-rebuilds using Dockerfile
